Detectives attached to Lagos State Police Command have arrested two suspected kidnappers who abducted a two-year-old girl at the Mountain of Fire and Ministry (MFM) Church, Agege branch. The victim, Esther Ojo, was abducted on March 24, about 12:30p.m. from the regional headquarters of the church when she went to worship with her parents. The suspects, Nwaigbo Magnus and Sixths Osunwoke, were arrested by the Divisional Police Officer (DPO) in charge of Igando Police Station, Taiwo Kasumu, after a plainclothes detectives trailed the kidnappers to their hideout and rescued the baby. The state Police Public Relations Officer (PPRO), DSP Bala Elkana, said the suspects had demanded an undisclosed ransom from the victimâ€™s parents before they were arrested. Elkana said before the suspects were arrested, they kept changing their venue within Igando axis for about four hours in an attempt to collect ransom until they were attested by the police. The baby has since been recovered from the den of the kidnappers and reunited with her parents, Mr. and Mrs. Jame Oladipo Ojo. The state Commissioner of Police, Zubairu Muazu, has directed the Deputy Commissioner of Police in charge of the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department (SCIID), Panti, Yaba to investigate and charge the suspects to court.